\binom{k+1}{r}+\binom{k+1}{r+1} = \frac{(k+1)!}{r!((k+1)-r)!} + \frac{(k+1)!}{(r+1)!((k+1)-(r+1))!}
=\frac{(k+1)!(r+1)}{(r+1)!((k+1)-r)!} + \frac{(k+1)! \color{red}{(k-r)}}{(r+1)!((k+1)-(r+1))!\color{red}{(k-r)}}
=(k+1)!\frac{k+1}{(r+1)!((k+1)-r)!}
\binom{k+1}{r} = \frac{(k+1)!}{(k+1-r)!r!}
\binom{k+1}{r+1} = \frac{(k+1)!}{(k+1-(r+1))!(r+1)!} = \frac{(k+1)!}{(k-r)!(r+1)!}
